__Task 1__

* The idea is to first sort the pairs on the basis of their `b` values. Maintain a pointer `i` which starts from the first pair in the array.

* For any given `i` , we consider the pairs in the range `i` to `n-1` and, for this range the minumum value of `b` for any possible combination will be `v[i][1]` and this takes care of one part of the expression.

* For the remaining part, greedily pick the top `(k+1)/2` a values in the current range which will be assigned `+` sign and the smallest `k/2` values which will be assigned `-` sign in the sum expression. Maintaining these two sums is the in my opinion the most difficult part in this problem and I have done it using three multisets, I'm sure there can be more efficient techniques to do the same using priority queues.

